<DOC><DOCNO> AP880401-0316 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-01-88 1301EST</FILEID><FIRST>u f BC-TheWeekAhead     04-01 0193</FIRST><SECOND>BC-The Week Ahead,0218</SECOND><BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE><TEXT>   Here are the major business events and economic events scheduledfor the coming week (some dates are tentative):</TEXT><BYLINE>MONDAY, April 4</BYLINE><TEXT>      WASHINGTON _ The Supreme Court issues orders and decisions.   WASHINGTON _ Congress is in recess until April 11.</TEXT><BYLINE>TUESDAY, April 5</BYLINE><TEXT>      WASHINGTON _ Arthur Levitt, chairman of the American StockExchange, is the luncheon speaker at the National Press Club.   KANSAS CITY, Mo. _ The Chrysler bargaining council of the UnitedAuto Workers union begins a three-day session to work out itsposition for contract talks with the automaker, which are to beginin mid-April.</TEXT><BYLINE>WEDNESDAY, April 6</BYLINE><TEXT>      DETROIT _ U.S. and foreign automakers are to report their salesof cars and light trucks during March.</TEXT><BYLINE>THURSDAY, April 7</BYLINE><TEXT>      NEW YORK _ The nation's biggest general retailers are to reporttheir March sales.</TEXT><BYLINE>FRIDAY, April 8</BYLINE><TEXT>      Nothing scheduled.</TEXT><BYLINE>SATURDAY, April 9</BYLINE><TEXT>      VIENNA, Austria _ OPEC's pricing committee is to meet to discussways of propping up oil prices.   LAS VEGAS, Nev. _ The National Association of Broadcastersbegins a four-day meeting.</TEXT></DOC>